Data analysis

Text

fse

We fitted a linear mixed model (estimated using REML and nloptwrap optimizer) to predict fse with group and time_point (formula: fse ~ 1 + group + time_point + group * time_point). The model included login_id as random effect (formula: ~1 | login_id). The models total explanatory power is substantial (conditional R2 = 0.71) and the part related to the fixed effects alone (marginal R2) is of 0.04. The models intercept, corresponding to group = control and time_point = 1st , is at 17.61 (S.E. = 0.70, p < .001, 95% CI [16.23, 18.99]). Within this model:

  • The effect of group [treatment] is statistically non-significant and negative (beta = -0.46, S.E. = 0.99, p = 0.643, 95% CI [-2.39, 1.48]; Std. beta = -0.11, 95% CI [-0.59, 0.37])
  • The effect of time point [2nd] is statistically non-significant and negative (beta = -0.43, S.E. = 0.79, p = 0.589, 95% CI [-1.97, 1.12]; Std. beta = -0.11, 95% CI [-0.49, 0.28])
  • The interaction effect of time point [2nd] on group [treatment] is statistically significant and positive (beta = 3.09, S.E. = 1.15, p = 0.007, 95% CI [0.83, 5.36]; Std. beta = 0.77, 95% CI [0.21, 1.33])

Standardized parameters were obtained by fitting the model on a standardized version of the dataset. 95% Confidence Intervals (CIs) and p-values were computed using a Wald normal distribution approximation.
